  "prompt": "What resorts in Renuka Lake Tourist-spots would be safe for unmarried couples, without the harassment of police, hotel staff, and moral police?",
  "response": "When traveling as an unmarried couple in India, including places like Renuka Lake in Himachal Pradesh, it's prudent to choose accommodations where privacy and respect for guests are top priorities. Here are a few tips to ensure a pleasant stay:\n\n1. **Research Online:** Look for reviews on platforms like TripAdvisor, Google, or Booking.com. Guest reviews can provide insight into how a hotel treats unmarried couples.\n\n2. **Call Ahead:** Contact the hotel directly to confirm their policies. Ensure they accept IDs of guests who are not married to each other.\n\n3. **Choose Reputable Hotels:** Opt for well-known or branded hotels, as they are more likely to respect privacy and adhere to professional standards.\n\n4. **Use Booking Apps:** Apps like OYO have specific filters for \"couple-friendly\" hotels, which indicate that the hotel welcomes unmarried couples.\n\n5. **Check Policies:** Make sure to check the hotel\u2019s policy on IDs at check-in. Avoid any property that seems to have restrictive or unclear rules regarding couples.\n\n6. **Privacy Assurances:** Look for hotels that explicitly assure privacy and have policies against sharing guest information with third parties.\n\nWhen booking a stay, prioritize places known for hospitality and positive guest treatment to help ensure a comfortable experience.",
